		<title>MIG Fonds and Bayern Kapital Back mbiomics €30M Raise</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/mig-fonds-and-bayern-kapital-back-mbiomics-e30m-raise/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 11:06:26 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200423</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>In a significant milestone for the European &#8216;techbio&#8217; industry, Mbiomics GmbH, based in Munich, announced that it had finalised the third and final closing of its Series A investment round,</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/mig-fonds-and-bayern-kapital-back-mbiomics-e30m-raise/" data-wpel-link="internal">MIG Fonds and Bayern Kapital Back mbiomics €30M Raise</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In a significant milestone for the European &#8216;techbio&#8217; industry, </span><a href="https://mbiomics.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Mbiomics </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">GmbH, based in Munich, announced that it had finalised the third and final closing of its Series A investment </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/uk-ai-startup-ineffable-raises-1-1b-seed-round/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">round</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, which now totals €30 million following a €12 million sub-session. </span>This will afford the company the capital it needs to move from platform-building phase to the clinical execution stage. The Series B was heavily oversubscribed, with leading existing investors MIG Fonds (Germany) and Bayern Kapital.</p>
<h2>Bridging the Gap: From Lab to Large-Scale Manufacturing</h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Mbiomics was founded in 2020 by Dr Johannes B. Woehrstein, Dr Laura Figulla and Dr Markus Rinecker and is one of the few startups working on one of the biggest engineering challenges within biotech: microbial consortia. Although the potential of the human gut microbiome in clinical research is well established, that potential has been hard to translate into a scalable, pharma-grade product.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200425" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200425" class="size-large wp-image-200425" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/DNA-Helix-1024x576.jpg" alt="DNA Helix" width="1024" height="576" /><p id="caption-attachment-200425" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The majority of current microbiome therapies are general FMTs, which are effective but naturally complex, hard to make uniform and heavily subject to regulatory approval. Mbiomics is overcoming these constraints by creating a live biotherapeutic product (LBP).</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Translating microbiome-based therapeutics into a deliverable product has eluded engineers for years,&#8221; said Dr Woehrstein, CEO and Co-Founder of mbiomics. &#8220;We are tackling this problem by building out the complete technology stack to enable the design, analysis, screening and manufacture of complex microbial consortia.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/uk-ai-startup-ineffable-raises-1-1b-seed-round/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">UK AI Startup Ineffable Raises $1.1B Seed Round</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Clinical Focus: Enhancing Cancer Immunotherapy</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This additional capital is likely to primarily benefit the company’s lead candidate, MBX-116. This candidate is currently being developed for use in combination with treatment with immune checkpoint inhibitors for patients with advanced melanoma.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Clinical studies have indicated that the gut microbiome is essential to patients&#8217; immune system response to cancer treatment. Majority of patients have efficacy of immunotherapy, but Mbiomics plans to &#8220;prime&#8221; the immune system by re-establishing microbial society. The company plans to conduct a Phase 1b study for MBX,116 in 2027.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Powerful &#8220;Techbio&#8221; Platform</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Mbiomics, through its proprietary analytical platform, leverages artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) to design microbial communities. The technology stack includes:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>High-Resolution Profiling:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Precision data generation to understand host-microbiome interactions.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Large-Scale Co-Cultivation:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> The ability to grow complex groups of bacteria together at a commercial scale.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Patient Stratification:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Using data to identify which patients are most likely to respond to specific microbial treatments.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Since our initial investment, the team has made impressive progress in translating microbiome science into a scalable therapeutic approach,&#8221; noted Dr Matthias Kromayer, Managing Partner of MIG Capital. &#8220;The company is now heading into clinical validation with great momentum.&#8221;</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Looking Ahead: Expanding the Pipeline</span></h2>
<p>While oncology takes precedence, the €30M fundraise will also fuel mbiomics&#8217; R&amp;D into further chronic diseases. The company is exploring the &#8216;gut-brain&#8217; and &#8216;gut-immune&#8217; axes, aiming to develop drugs for autoimmune diseases and neurodegeneration.</p>
<p>Having set up its own GMP-compliant development and production facility, Mbiomics has established itself as one of the frontrunners. Within the unexploited novel arena of synthetic microbial consortia and hopes to establish a new pharmaceutical benchmark for gut health.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/mig-fonds-and-bayern-kapital-back-mbiomics-e30m-raise/" data-wpel-link="internal">MIG Fonds and Bayern Kapital Back mbiomics €30M Raise</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
