		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 10:23:32 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200417</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>European startup All3 has announced that it has raised an impressive $25 million in seed funding. The round, co-led by RTP Global, is intended to speed up the deployment of</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/all3-secures-25m-for-ai-powered-construction-robots/" data-wpel-link="internal">All3 Secures $25M for AI-Powered Construction Robots</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">European startup </span><a href="https://all3.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">All3 </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has announced that it has raised an impressive $25 million in seed </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/uk-ai-startup-ineffable-raises-1-1b-seed-round/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. The round, co-led by RTP Global, is intended to speed up the deployment of autonomous, legged robots that will shake up the housing market.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The investment saw significant participation from SuperSeed, along with VNV Global, s16vc, and Begin Capital. As part of the deal, RTP Global Partner Jelmer de Jong will join All3’s board of directors.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Tackling the Construction Stagnation</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The traditional construction industry has largely failed to benefit from this trend. Construction productivity has failed to increase at the same rate as other industries. Despite some signs of improvement, it is clear that construction has stagnated. In 2026, a construction project will look similar to one completed in 1976, using the same assembly lines and repetitive, manual work. All3, founded by serial entrepreneurs Rodion Shishkov and Slava Bocharov, the duo behind the $1.5 billion food delivery giant Samokat, aims to end this &#8220;productivity drought&#8221;.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200420" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200420" class="size-large wp-image-200420" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Construction-site-1024x683.jpg" alt="Construction site" width="1024" height="683" /><p id="caption-attachment-200420" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“Construction is the largest global sector yet to experience a productivity revolution,” said Shishkov, CEO of All3. “With this funding, we’ll scale deployment of our technology with one clear mission: to solve the housing crisis once and for all.”</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/uk-ai-startup-ineffable-raises-1-1b-seed-round/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">UK AI Startup Ineffable Raises $1.1B Seed Round</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Mantis: A Robot That Walks the Walk</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">At the heart of All3’s technological stack is the Mantis, an autonomous-legged robot. Compared to conventional wheeled machines that struggle to traverse the muck, rough terrain, and vertical obstacles of a working building site, the Mantis is designed to overcome any obstacles. The Mantis is merely a mode of transportation. It is actually a specialized assembly unit.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Working in tandem with All3’s proprietary AI design software, the robot can assemble modular components with millimeter precision. The company’s &#8220;vertical integration&#8221; model means they handle almost everything above the concrete foundation, from AI-assisted architectural planning to the final move-in-ready structure.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Vertical Integration and Sustainability</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">All3’s approach differs from competitors who typically focus on a single niche, such as 3D printing walls or robotic bricklaying. Instead, All3 has rebuilt the entire construction value chain:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>AI Design Platform:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Already used to process over 100,000 square meters of residential projects.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Robotic Factories:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Manufacturing customized structural timber composite components.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>On-Site Assembly:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Deployed via the Mantis fleet to minimize human error and physical risk.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">According to the company, this integrated system reduces project costs by 30% and time to completion by 50%. Coupled with the use of timber composites and accurate assembly, the company anticipates a 25% lower embodied carbon than concrete and steel alternatives.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Scaling Across Europe</span></h2>
<p>With R&amp;D facilities in London and Belgrade and operational offices in Berlin and Zug, All3 is positioning itself as a Pan-European powerhouse. The new capital will be used to grow the engineering team and deploy its first commercial fleet of robots on residential projects in Germany, which serves as the company&#8217;s primary launch market.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The construction industry has long been a &#8220;graveyard for startups&#8221; due to the sheer complexity of physical sites. However, with the backing of RTP Global and a leadership team with a track record of billion-dollar exits, All3 might just be the firm to finally bring the assembly line to the construction site.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/all3-secures-25m-for-ai-powered-construction-robots/" data-wpel-link="internal">All3 Secures $25M for AI-Powered Construction Robots</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
