		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200408</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Contemporary Amperex Technology Co. Limited (CATL), the world’s largest EV battery manufacturer, has completed a HK$39.2 billion ($5 billion) share placement, a record for any Hong Kong share market so</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/catl-raises-5b-in-hong-kong-share-placement-deal/" data-wpel-link="internal">CATL Raises $5B in Hong Kong Share Placement Deal</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.catl.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Contemporary Amperex Technology Co. Limited</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> (CATL), the world’s largest EV battery manufacturer, has completed a HK$39.2 billion ($5 billion) share placement, a record for any Hong Kong share market so far this year. The deal completes on April 28, 2026.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Ningde-based company finalised the </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/audion-raises-15m-to-expand-audio-advertising-tech/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">sale </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">of some 62.4M new H shares at HK$628.20 each. The sale was at the tight end of the marketed range, which provided a 7% discount to the previous day&#8217;s close, but was oversubscribed, with demand said to be &#8216;frenzied&#8217;. The oversubscribed bookbuild was said to have included over 150 institutional investors, a diverse range of global hedge funds and long-only asset managers.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Capitalizing on the &#8220;Green Wave&#8221;</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Analysts reckon the placement is both opportunistic and strategic. CATL&#8217;s second listing on the Hong Kong exchange in May 2025 has seen its Hong Kong-listed share price rocket more than 150% since the issue price. By raising funds at this point, the company is &#8216;cementing in&#8217; investor capital while its valuation is still close to historic highs, driven by the worldwide shift to green energy as well as the rise in oil prices that has seen the EV take-up rate go up a pace.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200409" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200409" class="size-large wp-image-200409" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/car-dashboard-1024x683.jpg" alt="car dashboard" width="1024" height="683" /><p id="caption-attachment-200409" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The placement came after a busy week of shareholder activity. In the week before placement, there was a significant block trade in Shenzhen and a sale of $770 million by a Sinopec unit. Aside from these activities on the secondary market, the placement by CATL itself shows the company has a distinct desire to strengthen its own balance sheet in the face of a huge capital expenditure cycle.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/audion-raises-15m-to-expand-audio-advertising-tech/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Audion Raises $15M to Expand Audio Advertising Tech</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Fueling Global Expansion and Innovation</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $5 billion raise will be allocated for the four strategic pillars of CATL from 2026 to 2030:</span></p>
<ol>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Overseas manufacturing footprint</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: A large part of these proceeds will go into building up and scaling up the 7.3 billion euro battery plant in Hungary. This additional gigafactory is pivotal in enabling CATL to bypass possible trade walls.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Zero-Carbon Projects</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: CATL is investing heavily in &#8220;zero-carbon&#8221; factories and recycling processes, intending to be at the forefront of battery emission requirements as they become more stringent for European and North American regulators.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Research &amp; Development</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: The battery manufacturer is still working to improve energy density and charge speeds. Capital will help to develop the new 15C sodium-ion batteries, along with Shenxing ultra-fast charge cells.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Supply Chain Security</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: In light of geopolitical turbulence, CATL also recently greenlit billions of new capital to its mining and raw material businesses so that it could procure lithium and other critical minerals.</span></li>
</ol>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Market Leadership Amidst Competition</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Although CATL continues to dominate with a 40%+ share of the global EV battery market, the fundraising comes as it is under increased pressure domestically from BYD and internationally from Korean competitors such as LG Energy Solution. Raising the $5 billion in new liquidity signals to investors the &#8220;dry powder&#8221; to compete in a long, low-margin, high-cycle war of attrition.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8216;This is a clear message of intent,&#8217; added a senior analyst covering the Asian energy space. &#8216;CATL is not just defending its patch; it&#8217;s creating the infrastructure to control the whole energy transition environment, from the mines all the way through to the recycling facilities.&#8217;</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/catl-raises-5b-in-hong-kong-share-placement-deal/" data-wpel-link="internal">CATL Raises $5B in Hong Kong Share Placement Deal</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
